http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/Honour-for-Kathakali-artiste/article13987890.ece

Kathakali artiste Nelliyod Vasudevan Namboodiri has been selected for Guru Gopinath Natya Puraskara, an award in the name of the famed classical dancer, Guru Gopinath. The award comprises Rs.25,000 and a citation.Addressing a press conference here, vice-chairman of Guru Gopinath Natanagramam D. Sudarshanan said the award committee had decided to confer the award on Mr. Namboodiri, considering his immense contribution to Kathakali.Chief Minister Oommen Chandy will present the award at a function to be held in the city on January 13. Minister for Culture K.C. Joseph will attend the function. The Guru Gopinath Natanagramam is an undertaking of the State Department of Cultural Affairs.â€“ Special Correspondent